The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Ponting to play for Somerset
London: Ricky Ponting will play for English County Somerset later this year, the club said in a statement. Dashing batsman Ponting, currently leading Australia in Sri Lanka, will be available for the final stages of the 20-20 competition and the semi-final of the C amp; G Trophy, English crickets domestic one-day knockout competition in July. Somerset also said they hoped to have Ponting available for four National League (one-day) league games against Worcestershire, Sussex, Yorkshire and Durham. The clubs statement added: He will also play in four championship matches against Glamorgan, Hampshire, Durham and Yorkshire. Meanwhile, Somerset also announced that England fast bowler Andy Caddick had agreed a new four-year deal that would keep him at the County until the end of the 2007.  (AFP)  Copyright 
